WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.965 --> 00:00:09.205
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

2
00:00:10.245 --> 00:00:12.485
(SHEEP BLEATING)

3
00:00:13.525 --> 00:00:15.845
(DRUM RHYTHM STARTS)

4
00:00:17.765 --> 00:00:20.085
(MORE PERCUSSION JOINS RHYTHM)

5
00:00:23.205 --> 00:00:25.205
(FLUTE TUNE BEGINS)

6
00:00:27.125 --> 00:00:29.445
(CHEERFUL GUITAR TUNE)

7
00:00:31.445 --> 00:00:34.165
GIRL: 'Chemistry is everything.'
(MUSIC FADES)

8
00:00:34.245 --> 00:00:37.845
'Energy. elements. invisible bonds.

9
00:00:38.645 --> 00:00:41.685
And me. Flavia de Luce.

10
00:00:42.565 --> 00:00:45.285
I inherited my love of both
chemistry and adventure

11
00:00:45.685 --> 00:00:47.765
from my mother. Harriet.
whose lab this is.'

12
00:00:49.205 --> 00:00:50.805
(BLEATING CONTINUES OUTSIDE)

13
00:00:52.485 --> 00:00:54.565
'In fact. I was almost born

14
00:00:54.965 --> 00:00:56.805
on one of her adventures
during the war.

15
00:00:56.885 --> 00:00:58.405
according to Father.'

16
00:00:58.565 --> 00:01:00.805
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
Mmm. Mmm!

17
00:01:00.965 --> 00:01:03.205
Glad to see
your appetite's come back.

18
00:01:03.285 --> 00:01:04.805
Mmm. mmm!

19
00:01:04.965 --> 00:01:07.445
It's these knafehs.
I just can't stop eating them.

20
00:01:08.325 --> 00:01:10.085
Oh. dear. I am awful.

21
00:01:10.405 --> 00:01:11.685
(SIGHS) Right.

22
00:01:12.085 --> 00:01:13.925

23
23
00:01:13.925 --> 00:01:16.085
I'm off to see a man about a stamp.

24
00:01:16.245 --> 00:01:18.325
What. another?
This one. my darling.

25
00:01:18.485 --> 00:01:20.485
is a British Guyana
two-cent Cotton-Reel

26
00:01:20.885 --> 00:01:22.245
once owned by King Farouk.

27
00:01:22.405 --> 00:01:23.845
Gosh. how thrilling.
(CHUCKLES)

28
00:01:24.245 --> 00:01:25.925
(CHUCKLES) Mmm.
Goodbye. Ratty.

29
00:01:26.005 --> 00:01:27.605
Goodbye. Mole.
Mmm.

30
00:01:27.685 --> 00:01:29.205
Oh. may I?

31
00:01:29.285 --> 00:01:30.885
Go on. then.
Mmm.

32
00:01:30.965 --> 00:01:32.885
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

33
00:01:33.925 --> 00:01:35.925
(GENTLE. CURIOUS MUSIC)

34
00:01:37.605 --> 00:01:39.365
(VEHICLE ENGINE PASSES)

35
00:01:41.685 --> 00:01:43.205
{\an8}(IN GERMAN)

36
00:01:43.365 --> 00:01:44.885
{\an8}(IN GERMAN)

37
00:01:47.365 --> 00:01:49.445
(MUSIC RHYTHM BUILDS)

38
00:01:50.885 --> 00:01:53.365
(LOUD. OVERLAPPING CHATTER)
(HORN HONKING)

39
00:01:58.725 --> 00:02:01.205
(MUSIC LULLS)

40
00:02:04.085 --> 00:02:05.365
Madam!

41
00:02:06.405 --> 00:02:08.405
(CURIOUS MUSIC RESUMES)

42
00:02:09.285 --> 00:02:12.085
{\an8}(IN ARABIC)

43
00:02:12.245 --> 00:02:13.525
{\an8}Ah!

44
00:02:14.565 --> 00:02:15.605
(SIGHS) Ah...

45
00:02:15.765 --> 00:02:16.725
{\an8}(IN ARABIC)

46
00:02:17.125 --> 00:02:18.405
{\an8}(TENSE NOTE)

47
00:02:18.485 --> 00:02:19.525
{\an8}(IN ARABIC)

48
00:02:22.725 --> 00:02:24.005
{\an8}(LOUDLY. IN ARABIC)

49
00:02:24.165 --> 00:02:25.445
(GASPS)
(WHISTLES)

50
00:02:25.605 --> 00:02:27.685
(SHOUTS IN ARABIC)
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

51
00:02:28.805 --> 00:02:30.965
{\an8}(IN ARABIC)

52
00:02:31.845 --> 00:02:33.525
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

53
00:02:33.605 --> 00:02:34.885
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

54
00:02:34.965 --> 00:02:36.405
(GASPING) Ooh.

55
00:02:36.485 --> 00:02:37.925
(OVERLAPPING SHOUTS)

56
00:02:38.325 --> 00:02:40.005
(PANTING)
Courage. my love. We can do this.

57
00:02:40.085 --> 00:02:42.565
(OVERLAPPING SHOUTS)

58
00:02:42.725 --> 00:02:44.005
(SIGHS)

59
00:02:44.085 --> 00:02:45.445
Havilland? (PANTING)
Hmm?

60
00:02:45.765 --> 00:02:48.085
Harriet. what's going on?
Can't talk. darling!

61
00:02:48.165 --> 00:02:50.245
(TENSE MUSIC)
Isee.

62
00:02:50.565 --> 00:02:51.845
Don't worry. we'll shake 'em.

63
00:02:52.005 --> 00:02:54.085
(SHOUTING IN GERMAN)
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

64
00:02:54.245 --> 00:02:57.045
(GUNSHOTS)
(PANICKED SHOUTING)

65
00:02:57.205 --> 00:02:58.725
Alright. darling
Yes. alright.

66
00:02:59.045 --> 00:03:01.285
(TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES)

67
00:03:01.685 --> 00:03:03.125
Car.
Right.

68
00:03:03.445 --> 00:03:06.325
I can get us to London in four days.
Three if the wind is with us.

69
00:03:06.645 --> 00:03:09.125
(HINGES SQUEAK) Harriet. next time
The Nest sends you on a mission.

70
00:03:09.205 --> 00:03:10.645
could you let me know about it?
(GRUNTS)

71
00:03:11.525 --> 00:03:13.685
(SiGHS) You know I'm not
allowed to discuss it.

72
00:03:14.085 --> 00:03:16.805
Perhaps when we get to the airfield.
I should take the yoke.

73
00:03:16.885 --> 00:03:19.205
I know it's your plane. but...
OK. I suppose just this once.

74
00:03:19.365 --> 00:03:21.205
(GUNSHOTS)
Ooh. Oh!

75
00:03:21.365 --> 00:03:24.325
Do hurry. darling. or there'll be
three of us on the plane.

76
00:03:24.405 --> 00:03:25.605
(GUNSHOT)
(ENGINE REVS)

77
00:03:25.925 --> 00:03:26.965
OK. ready? (PANTING)

78
00:03:27.125 --> 00:03:29.045
Oh! Ready.
(SIGHS)

79
00:03:29.445 --> 00:03:31.765
(ENGINE ROARS)
(GUNFIRE)

80
00:03:31.845 --> 00:03:33.125
(HORN HONKING)

81
00:03:33.445 --> 00:03:35.765
(GRAND. RHYTHMIC MUSIC)

82
00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:43.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

83
00:03:44.645 --> 00:03:46.805
(AEROPLANE ENGINE RUMBLING)

84
00:03:47.845 --> 00:03:50.005
(MUSIC BUILDS)

85
00:03:54.485 --> 00:03:56.965
(MUSIC CONCLUDES)
(COOING)

86
00:03:57.125 --> 00:03:59.205
Isn't she perfect?
She is. (CHUCKLES)

87
00:03:59.285 --> 00:04:01.445
(APPROACHING FOOTSTEPS)
Oh!

88
00:04:01.605 --> 00:04:03.205
Harriet. Havilland.

89
00:04:03.365 --> 00:04:05.525
Auntie. (SIGHS)
Daphne and Ophelia.

90
00:04:05.605 --> 00:04:08.085
Good morning. Aunt Felicity.
Mrs Mullet.

91
00:04:08.245 --> 00:04:11.285
(SHEEP BLEATING)
Well. let's see this baby.

92
00:04:11.365 --> 00:04:13.605
Girls. follow me. please.

93
00:04:14.645 --> 00:04:15.925
(GURGLES)

94
00:04:16.085 --> 00:04:18.485
Moldwarp.
(WHISPERS) Pignut.

95
00:04:18.645 --> 00:04:20.085
(COOS)
Felicity. meet

96
00:04:20.405 --> 00:04:22.805
Flavia Sabine de Luce.
(COOS)

97
00:04:22.885 --> 00:04:25.765
Yes. indeed.
(SOFT. CURIOUS MUSIC BEGINS)

98
00:04:25.845 --> 00:04:28.165
We have a new fledgling in The Nest.

99
00:04:28.485 --> 00:04:30.565
I think she might just
have the stuff. Mmm. (CHUCKLES)

100
00:04:30.725 --> 00:04:32.965
(COOS)
Right then. I haven't much time.

101
00:04:33.365 --> 00:04:36.165
Ah. Our Cairo agent
gave me this shawl.

102
00:04:36.405 --> 00:04:38.165
Here you are.
Yes.

103
00:04:38.485 --> 00:04:40.405
Let's see..
(SOFTLY) Hmm.

104
00:04:40.485 --> 00:04:43.365
Knit. purl. Knit. knit. purl.
(CHUCKLES)

105
00:04:43.685 --> 00:04:46.805
(INHALES) Some kind of secret code.

106
00:04:46.965 --> 00:04:48.485
Well done. Harriet.

107
00:04:48.565 --> 00:04:50.245
This will ruin Hitler's day.

108
00:04:50.565 --> 00:04:52.485
(INHALES) MrS Mullet?

109
00:04:52.565 --> 00:04:54.085
Yes. ma'am.

110
00:04:55.445 --> 00:04:56.805
Hmm.

111
00:04:57.125 --> 00:04:59.125
(COOING)
(GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES)

112
00:04:59.445 --> 00:05:01.285
(SIGHS)
(CHUCKLES)

113
00:05:01.685 --> 00:05:03.125
Hmm.

114
00:05:03.445 --> 00:05:05.685
(SiNGS) # See the pyramids

115
00:05:06.085 --> 00:05:08.725
(COOING)
# Along the Nile

116
00:05:10.085 --> 00:05:12.165
# Watch the sunrise

117
00:05:12.245 --> 00:05:14.405
# On a tropic isle

118
00:05:14.725 --> 00:05:16.805
(RECORDING OF "YOU BELONG TO ME"
BY JO STAFFORD FADES IN)

119
00:05:16.965 --> 00:05:18.805
# But just remember. darling

120
00:05:19.125 --> 00:05:21.925
# All the while

121
00:05:22.725 --> 00:05:27.045
# You belong to me #

122
00:05:27.445 --> 00:05:29.845
{\an8}(SONG FADES OUT)

123
00:05:30.005 --> 00:05:33.125
'Mother taught me that
chemistry is the story

124
00:05:33.445 --> 00:05:35.605
of how everything.
the whole of creation.

125
00:05:35.765 --> 00:05:38.885
is held together
by invisible bonds.

126
00:05:39.765 --> 00:05:42.405
And the more energy
you put into these bonds.

127
00:05:42.805 --> 00:05:44.805
the harder they are to break.

128
00:05:45.925 --> 00:05:47.765
If only it were the
same for families.

129
00:05:48.085 --> 00:05:49.365
(TWO KNOCKS ON DOOR)

130
00:05:49.445 --> 00:05:50.965
(MUFFLED) Flavia. open up.

131
00:05:51.285 --> 00:05:52.805
What's the password?

132
00:05:52.885 --> 00:05:54.645
Open up! It's an emergency.

133
00:05:54.725 --> 00:05:56.325
(CURIOUS MUSIC STOPS)
(SIGHS)

134
00:05:56.405 --> 00:05:58.005
(HINGES SQUEAK)

135
00:05:58.325 --> 00:05:59.765
What kind of emergency?

136
00:06:00.165 --> 00:06:01.765
What have you done
with Mummy's pearls.

137
00:06:02.085 --> 00:06:03.925
you odious prawn?
(GASPS)

138
00:06:04.005 --> 00:06:05.685
We know you filched them.

139
00:06:06.005 --> 00:06:07.925
I'm not the keeper of your trinkets.

140
00:06:08.005 --> 00:06:09.925
Moldwarp.
Pignut.

141
00:06:10.005 --> 00:06:12.485
Why do you two always gang up on me?

142
00:06:13.365 --> 00:06:15.525
Shall we tell her?
It's time.

143
00:06:16.885 --> 00:06:18.725
We're not really your sisters.

144
00:06:18.805 --> 00:06:20.085
What?
Mummy picked you up

145
00:06:20.405 --> 00:06:22.325
at the home for unwed mothers.
(CHUCKLES)

146
00:06:22.645 --> 00:06:23.685
I don't believe you.

147
00:06:23.845 --> 00:06:26.565
Besides. everyone always says
I look just like Harriet.

148
00:06:26.885 --> 00:06:28.405
Oh. yes. that's why she chose you.

149
00:06:28.725 --> 00:06:30.005
Because of the resemblance.

150
00:06:30.405 --> 00:06:31.845
That's ridiculous!
No. honestly.

151
00:06:32.085 --> 00:06:33.605
I'll never forget Mummy...
(BUBBLING)

152
00:06:34.005 --> 00:06:36.085
(GASPS)
(BUBBLING AND SIZZLING)

153
00:06:36.325 --> 00:06:38.565
(TENSE MUSIC STARTS)
(GASPS)

154
00:06:38.965 --> 00:06:40.405
Those were Mummy's pearls.

155
00:06:41.685 --> 00:06:43.445
She left them for me.

156
00:06:43.525 --> 00:06:46.005
Do you want to know something else?

157
00:06:46.405 --> 00:06:48.085
You're the reason
Mummy never came back.

158
00:06:48.965 --> 00:06:52.325
She couldn't bear to look at
your ugly face a moment longer.

159
00:06:52.405 --> 00:06:55.125
(INHALES SHARPLY. SCREAMS)

160
00:06:55.125 --> 00:06:56.485
(TENSE MUSIC STOPS)

161
00:06:56.805 --> 00:06:58.325
(CLOCK TICKING. BIRDS CHIRPING)

162
00:06:58.645 --> 00:07:00.165
(SIGHS) Rubbish.

163
00:07:01.285 --> 00:07:04.725
Any fool can see
it's an or dinary mis-per foration.

164
00:07:06.725 --> 00:07:08.565
Good morning. Father. dear.
Ah.

165
00:07:08.645 --> 00:07:10.885
Girls. No sign of Flavia?

166
00:07:11.205 --> 00:07:13.205
It's nearly 12.

167
00:07:13.285 --> 00:07:15.045
NDIMA
(TENSE. MISCHIEVOUS MUSIC)

168
00:07:15.365 --> 00:07:17.045
(MUFFLED SHOUTING)

169
00:07:17.125 --> 00:07:19.045
(MONKEYS SCREECHING)

170
00:07:19.125 --> 00:07:21.125
'Charles Darwin once said

171
00:07:21.205 --> 00:07:23.445
that the fiercest competition
for survival

172
00:07:23.525 --> 00:07:25.445
comes from one's own tribe.

173
00:07:25.765 --> 00:07:27.685
Clearly. he had sisters.'
(PANTING)

174
00:07:27.765 --> 00:07:29.685
No. this won't do.

175
00:07:30.085 --> 00:07:33.365
I always say better three hours
too early than a minute too late.

176
00:07:33.525 --> 00:07:36.325
(GASPS)
(TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES)

177
00:07:36.405 --> 00:07:37.925
To tell you the truth. Father.

178
00:07:38.005 --> 00:07:40.405
Daphne and I are quite concerned
about Flavia.

179
00:07:40.565 --> 00:07:42.965
It's true.
She's becoming positively feral.

180
00:07:43.045 --> 00:07:44.325
Feral?

181
00:07:45.445 --> 00:07:46.965
(MUSIC INTENSIFIES)

182
00:07:47.045 --> 00:07:48.085
(LOCK CLICKS)

183
00:07:48.405 --> 00:07:50.085
(CHIMING. CUCKOO CHIRPING)

184
00:07:50.405 --> 00:07:52.005
(CLOCK CHIMING LOUDLY)

185
00:07:52.325 --> 00:07:53.605
(TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES)

186
00:07:53.765 --> 00:07:55.205
(LOCK CLICKS)
(GASPS)

187
00:07:55.525 --> 00:07:55.765
(PANTING)

188
00:07:55.765 --> 00:07:56.005
IDIMA
(PANTING)

189
00:07:56.005 --> 00:07:56.645
(PANTING)

190
00:07:56.645 --> 00:07:57.365
NDIMA
(PANTING)

191
00:07:57.605 --> 00:08:00.645
in Uncle Tar's laboratory
doing God knows what.

192
00:08:00.805 --> 00:08:01.605
(PANTING)

193
00:08:02.005 --> 00:08:03.525
Well. your mother loved
that laboratory.

194
00:08:03.925 --> 00:08:06.485
(CLOCK CHIMING)
(PANTING) Oh...

195
00:08:06.645 --> 00:08:08.725
She used Mummy's pearls
as one of her beastly experiments.

196
00:08:09.205 --> 00:08:09.845
You wouldn't believe the things
that come out of her mouth.

197
00:08:09.845 --> 00:08:11.925
believe the things
that come out

198
00:08:12.085 --> 00:08:13.045
Gadzooks!

199
00:08:14.005 --> 00:08:16.725
The other day. she told me to...
(WHISPERS) put a sock in it.

200
00:08:16.885 --> 00:08:18.885
Huh! I think
she gets it from the wireless.

201
00:08:19.285 --> 00:08:21.365
(BEAR ROARS)
(TENSE NOTES)

202
00:08:21.525 --> 00:08:23.765
She ought to be sent away. really
To a proper school.

203
00:08:23.845 --> 00:08:24.165

204
203
00:08:24.165 --> 00:08:24.885
Hmm.

205
00:08:25.045 --> 00:08:26.485
(CLOCK CHIMES)
(TENSE MUSIC STOPS)

206
00:08:29.365 --> 00:08:31.765
(CLICKS TONGUE)
Hello. Father. Sisters. dear.

207
00:08:35.045 --> 00:08:37.205
(INHALES DEEPLY)
Beast. how did you get out?

208
00:08:37.605 --> 00:08:39.445
You should've tied my thumbs
together. Moron.

209
00:08:39.605 --> 00:08:41.445
(SIGHS)
Flavia. a word.

210
00:08:41.605 --> 00:08:43.445
How was the royal
stamp exhibition. Father?

211
00:08:43.845 --> 00:08:45.445
You were going up to examine

212
00:08:45.845 --> 00:08:47.605
a pair of Inverted Jennies.
weren't you?

213
00:08:48.485 --> 00:08:50.405
(DISTANT CUTLERY CLATTERING)

214
00:08:53.605 --> 00:08:55.845
Well. Y- Yes.
Not- Not bad. thank you.

215
00:08:56.005 --> 00:08:57.925
But the. uh. the real excitement...
(SIGHS HEA VILY)

216
00:08:58.325 --> 00:09:00.165
..was a complete set
of Rhodesian Admir als.

217
00:09:00.565 --> 00:09:02.565
(CHUCKLES)
Father is incapable

218
00:09:02.885 --> 00:09:05.125
of thinking of stamps and discipline

219
00:09:05.285 --> 00:09:06.885
Entirely ungummed.

220
00:09:07.205 --> 00:09:09.205
Gosh! How thrilling.

221
00:09:09.365 --> 00:09:12.565
(RUSHING FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)
Here we are. Hot out the oven.

222
00:09:13.685 --> 00:09:16.325
(SIZZLING)
Baked rabbit and onions.

223
00:09:16.645 --> 00:09:18.325
Ohh. well. thank you. Mrs Mullet.

224
00:09:18.725 --> 00:09:21.125
And I've a special treat
for supper! (CHUCKLES)

225
00:09:21.525 --> 00:09:23.285
(INHALES) A custard pie.

226
00:09:23.445 --> 00:09:26.965
Ohhh. Really. Mrs Mullet.
you needn't go to such trouble.

227
00:09:27.365 --> 00:09:28.645
No trouble at all. sir.

228
00:09:28.725 --> 00:09:31.445
I know how the girls depreciate it.
(CHUCKLES)

229
00:09:31.605 --> 00:09:33.605
(RUSHING FOOTSTEPS DEPART)
(YELPS)

230
00:09:34.485 --> 00:09:36.485
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

231
00:09:36.645 --> 00:09:38.885
What is that?
A dead bird.

232
00:09:39.285 --> 00:09:41.685
One can see that. Flavia.
I meant on its beak.

233
00:09:46.645 --> 00:09:48.645
(OMINOUS MUSIC SOFTENS)

234
00:09:50.885 --> 00:09:52.405
Golly.

235
00:09:53.765 --> 00:09:56.085
It's a Penny Black. isn't it. Father?
(PANTING)

236
00:09:56.965 --> 00:09:59.445
(OMINOUS NOTES)

237
00:10:02.565 --> 00:10:04.485
Dispose of that thing.

238
00:10:04.645 --> 00:10:06.165
(MUSIC FADES OUT)
(SHOUTS) At once!

239
00:10:06.325 --> 00:10:08.485
Please. Mrs Mullet.

240
00:10:08.645 --> 00:10:10.005
Y- Yes. Colonel.

241
00:10:10.325 --> 00:10:11.925
That's all I need.

242
00:10:12.005 --> 00:10:13.685
to be to deposing dead birds.

243
00:10:14.085 --> 00:10:15.125
We're not done with you.

244
00:10:15.525 --> 00:10:16.565
Moldwarp.
Pignut.

245
00:10:16.965 --> 00:10:18.245
(SIGHS)

246
00:10:18.645 --> 00:10:20.165
(BIRD CHIRPING OUTSIDE)

247
00:10:21.285 --> 00:10:22.805
(SHUDDERS) Urgh!

248
00:10:23.125 --> 00:10:24.885
(CURIOUS MUSIC)

249
00:10:25.205 --> 00:10:26.565
Dogger!

250
00:10:26.885 --> 00:10:27.925
Wait for me!

251
00:10:28.805 --> 00:10:30.565
(PANTING)

252
00:10:30.725 --> 00:10:33.125
(INSECTS CHIRRUPING)
Small. brownish.

253
00:10:33.205 --> 00:10:34.885
with a stamp on its beak.

254
00:10:35.205 --> 00:10:36.485
A Penny Black.

255
00:10:37.285 --> 00:10:38.885
Odd.

256
00:10:39.205 --> 00:10:40.245
Yes. miss?

257
00:10:40.645 --> 00:10:45.125
Place contact arms B and C
directly on the lobes of cam D.

258
00:10:45.285 --> 00:10:47.285
Alright. Now. please...

259
00:10:47.365 --> 00:10:48.885
(ENGINE SPUTTERS)

260
00:10:49.045 --> 00:10:50.325
(SIGHS)
(SIGHS)

261
00:10:50.725 --> 00:10:52.005
Blast.

262
00:10:52.085 --> 00:10:53.445
Might it be the battery?

263
00:10:53.605 --> 00:10:54.885
Might be anything.

264
00:10:55.285 --> 00:10:57.285
Mrs Harriet
took such care of her car.

265
00:10:57.445 --> 00:10:59.525
but after she went away. she...

266
00:11:00.325 --> 00:11:02.085
Something wrong. miss?

267
00:11:03.045 --> 00:11:07.045
It's only that Daphne and Ophelia
were saying that I was adopted.

268
00:11:10.005 --> 00:11:11.605
Families.

269
00:11:12.405 --> 00:11:14.405
They're a bit like a chemistry set.

270
00:11:15.285 --> 00:11:17.525
Some people.
your sisters. for example.

271
00:11:18.645 --> 00:11:20.405
quite basic elements.

272
00:11:21.205 --> 00:11:23.045
Others are much rarer.

273
00:11:23.365 --> 00:11:24.645
Like argon.

274
00:11:25.525 --> 00:11:27.445
And you. miss.

275
00:11:29.605 --> 00:11:31.445
Thanks. Dogger.
(CHUCKLES)

276
00:11:31.605 --> 00:11:34.245
(CAR CREAKS. THUD)

277
00:11:35.045 --> 00:11:37.125
(SOFT CLANKING IN ENGINE)

278
00:11:37.285 --> 00:11:39.365
Uh. it's.
"Leaves of three. let it be."

279
00:11:39.445 --> 00:11:40.965
right?

280
00:11:41.125 --> 00:11:42.645
Poison ivy?

281
00:11:43.525 --> 00:11:45.285
I believe it was Confucius who said.

282
00:11:45.445 --> 00:11:47.365
'On a journey to revenge.

283
00:11:47.445 --> 00:11:49.365
be sure to dig two graves."

284
00:11:49.525 --> 00:11:51.685
(CURIOUS NOTES)
(CHUCKLES)

285
00:11:54.885 --> 00:11:57.205
(LOW. TENSE MUSIC)

286
00:12:01.125 --> 00:12:04.645
'Most chemists have a favourite
corner of their craft.

287
00:12:05.525 --> 00:12:07.685
Mine happens to be poisons.

288
00:12:09.365 --> 00:12:12.885
'This is the way the ancient
alchemists practised their art.'

289
00:12:15.365 --> 00:12:17.365
(LIQUID BUBBLING)
'Heat and steam.

290
00:12:17.765 --> 00:12:19.525
Action and reaction.

291
00:12:21.125 --> 00:12:23.525
Frost and flame.'

292
00:12:23.605 --> 00:12:26.405
(TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES)

293
00:12:28.005 --> 00:12:29.845
(MUSIC LULLS)
(F AINT SNORING)

294
00:12:30.165 --> 00:12:32.245
(MISCHIEVOUS MUSIC)

295
00:12:36.885 --> 00:12:38.325
(GROANS)

296
00:12:38.405 --> 00:12:40.165
Don't be so revolting. Flavia.

297
00:12:40.565 --> 00:12:41.525
(SIGHS)

298
00:12:44.405 --> 00:12:46.245
(MUSIC BUILDS)

299
00:12:49.125 --> 00:12:51.045
(MUSIC STOPS)
(DISTANT SHOUTING) Get out!

300
00:12:51.205 --> 00:12:53.285
MAN (FAINTLY):
You're not treating me like that?

301
00:12:53.685 --> 00:12:55.525
After all these years.
asking for favours.

302
00:12:55.925 --> 00:12:56.885
(CURIOUS MUSIC)

303
00:12:57.285 --> 00:12:58.885
Jacko. let's not argue.

304
00:12:59.765 --> 00:13:01.685
We used to be such friends.
didn't we?

305
00:13:03.525 --> 00:13:05.445
Don't you put on airs with me.
Jacko.

306
00:13:05.845 --> 00:13:07.685
After all. we've known each other

307
00:13:08.085 --> 00:13:10.165
since we were in short pants
at Greyminster.

308
00:13:10.245 --> 00:13:12.725
You are a loathsome. despicable...
(INHALES)

309
00:13:12.885 --> 00:13:14.965
(MUSIC STOPS)
Teesdale was too kind to you.

310
00:13:15.365 --> 00:13:17.685
Teesdale? Old Cuppa?

311
00:13:20.165 --> 00:13:21.445
(CHUCKLES)

312
00:13:21.765 --> 00:13:23.925
It's exactly 30 years since...

313
00:13:24.005 --> 00:13:25.605
(THROUGH TEETH) SinCe we killed him.

314
00:13:26.005 --> 00:13:27.285
(TENSE MUSIC STARTS)
Be reasonable.

315
00:13:27.445 --> 00:13:28.965
What's a couple of thousand to you?

316
00:13:29.045 --> 00:13:30.885
You must have come into a fair bit
when Harriet-

317
00:13:31.045 --> 00:13:32.245
Ah. ah. ah. ah!

318
00:13:32.405 --> 00:13:34.565
SHUT your filthy mouth.

319
00:13:34.965 --> 00:13:36.965
Now. what are you going
do with that. huh?

320
00:13:37.125 --> 00:13:38.645
Bash me over the head. huh?

321
00:13:38.805 --> 00:13:40.085
(CHUCKLING)

322
00:13:40.405 --> 00:13:43.125
You don't have it in you. Jacko.
Don't push me.

323
00:13:43.285 --> 00:13:44.885
(GASPS)
(TENSE MUSIC STOPS)

324
00:13:45.765 --> 00:13:48.325
(ARGUMENT CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY)

325
00:13:51.285 --> 00:13:52.645
(SIGHS)

326
00:13:56.725 --> 00:13:58.885
(INSECTS CHIRRUPING)
(CLOCK TICKING)

327
00:13:59.765 --> 00:14:01.365
(DISTANT FOOTSTEPS)

328
00:14:01.685 --> 00:14:02.965
(INHALES SHARPLY)

329
00:14:03.285 --> 00:14:04.645
(SCRAPING)

330
00:14:06.245 --> 00:14:08.085
(TICKING GROWS LOUDER)

331
00:14:08.165 --> 00:14:09.605
(DOOR CREAKING)

332
00:14:10.005 --> 00:14:11.925
(OMINOUS NOTE)

333
00:14:12.085 --> 00:14:14.485
(CURIOUS. SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

334
00:14:19.205 --> 00:14:20.725
(INHALES SHARPLY)

335
00:14:26.405 --> 00:14:27.765
(MUSIC ENDS)

336
00:14:27.845 --> 00:14:29.445
That's odd.

337
00:14:31.605 --> 00:14:34.325
(INSECTS CHIRRUPING)
(OWLI HOOTING)

338
00:14:34.485 --> 00:14:36.485
(CURIOUS MUSIC)

339
00:14:36.565 --> 00:14:38.645
(CHIRRUPING & HOOTING GETS LOUDER)

340
00:14:44.405 --> 00:14:46.725
(SIGHS)
Oh. Harriet. my love. where are you?

341
00:14:47.125 --> 00:14:48.645
(SNIFFLING)
(SOMBRE MUSIC)

342
00:14:49.765 --> 00:14:52.005
it's all catching up to me.

343
00:14:53.925 --> 00:14:55.765
(CR YING)

344
00:14:55.925 --> 00:14:57.925
(SOMBRE MUSIC)
(GASPS)

345
00:14:58.085 --> 00:14:59.925
(HITTING CAR)
Damn it! Damn it!

346
00:15:00.085 --> 00:15:01.445
(INHALES DEEPLY AND SIGHS)

347
00:15:02.325 --> 00:15:03.845
(GRUNTS)

348
00:15:05.285 --> 00:15:07.285
(SNIFFLES)
(INHALES)

349
00:15:07.445 --> 00:15:08.885
(SIGHS DEEPLY)
(MUSIC ENDS)

350
00:15:09.285 --> 00:15:10.485
(OWL HOOTING)

351
00:15:12.165 --> 00:15:13.445
Dogger?
(ANIMAL SCREECHES)

352
00:15:14.325 --> 00:15:16.165
Is that you?
(SCREECHES)

353
00:15:16.325 --> 00:15:17.525
(THUD)
(GRUNTS)

354
00:15:17.685 --> 00:15:18.965
(PANTING)

355
00:15:19.285 --> 00:15:20.325
(GASPS)

356
00:15:20.405 --> 00:15:22.405
(DRAMATIC NOTES)

357
00:15:22.485 --> 00:15:24.405
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

358
00:15:27.045 --> 00:15:29.205
Um... Are you..?

359
00:15:29.285 --> 00:15:30.805
(BREATH SHUDDERS)

360
00:15:31.765 --> 00:15:33.365
(INHALES SHARPLY)
(GASPS LOUDLY)

361
00:15:33.765 --> 00:15:35.285
Vah-lay!

362
00:15:35.365 --> 00:15:36.885
(WHEEZES)

363
00:15:37.285 --> 00:15:38.645
(UNSETTLING MUSIC)

364
00:15:38.805 --> 00:15:40.325
(GASPS)

365
00:15:40.645 --> 00:15:41.925
(SNIFFING. GASPS)

366
00:15:42.085 --> 00:15:44.965
(WHISPERED VOICEOVER)
'That smell. I know that smell!'

367
00:15:45.125 --> 00:15:46.725
(GASPS) Oh! (PANTING)

368
00:15:47.525 --> 00:15:49.525
(TENSE MUSIC)

369
00:15:52.405 --> 00:15:54.805
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)
(PANTING)

370
00:15:56.725 --> 00:15:58.405
There's a body.

371
00:15:58.485 --> 00:16:00.565
In the gar den! (PANTING)

372
00:16:01.925 --> 00:16:04.005
(CURIOUS MUSIC)

373
00:16:07.365 --> 00:16:08.965
Where's your father?

374
00:16:09.125 --> 00:16:10.645
He'S...

375
00:16:10.725 --> 00:16:12.405
in Harriet's car.

376
00:16:13.765 --> 00:16:16.005
I'll have to ring the police.

377
00:16:16.405 --> 00:16:18.565
(LIVELY RHYTHMIC MUSIC)

378
00:16:20.565 --> 00:16:22.165
(HANDBRAKE CLICKS)

379
00:16:26.485 --> 00:16:29.285
(MUSIC STOPS ABRUPTLY)
(BIRDS TWEETING)

380
00:16:29.445 --> 00:16:30.965
Good morning.

381
00:16:31.045 --> 00:16:32.325
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

382
00:16:34.005 --> 00:16:35.605
You must be Miss de Luce.

383
00:16:35.925 --> 00:16:37.205
Flavia. please.

384
00:16:37.285 --> 00:16:38.805
I'm Inspector Hewitt.

385
00:16:39.045 --> 00:16:42.005
This is Detective Sergeant Woolmer.
Detective Sergeant Graves.

386
00:16:42.405 --> 00:16:43.765
Is your father at home?
He is.

387
00:16:43.925 --> 00:16:45.845
But he's indisposed.

388
00:16:46.165 --> 00:16:47.685
(HURRIED FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

389
00:16:49.685 --> 00:16:51.445
Good morning. sir.
Morning

390
00:16:51.685 --> 00:16:53.285
Everything alright. Flavia?

391
00:16:53.605 --> 00:16:55.125
Perfectly. Mrs Mullet. Thank you.

392
00:16:55.285 --> 00:16:58.085
Well. Inspector. I suppose you'd
like to take a dekko at the corpse?

393
00:16:58.165 --> 00:16:59.685
Corpse. did you say?

394
00:17:00.085 --> 00:17:02.245
I'm afraid so. Mrs Mullet. Yes.

395
00:17:02.645 --> 00:17:04.245
Good Lord.
(CROW CAWS)

396
00:17:04.645 --> 00:17:06.405
Follow me. Inspector.

397
00:17:13.365 --> 00:17:15.125
(SIGHS)

398
00:17:15.205 --> 00:17:16.485
Hmm.

399
00:17:17.845 --> 00:17:19.845
(UNSETTLING MUSIC)

400
00:17:23.685 --> 00:17:25.445
(SOFT CRACKING SOUND)

401
00:17:27.365 --> 00:17:30.325
You'll notice signs of rigor mortis
and lividity.

402
00:17:31.685 --> 00:17:33.925
As well as early signs
of putrefaction.

403
00:17:35.125 --> 00:17:36.885
Thank you. Miss de Luce.

404
00:17:37.205 --> 00:17:38.485
We'll take it from here.

405
00:17:38.805 --> 00:17:40.325
Thank you.

406
00:17:40.405 --> 00:17:42.325
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

407
00:17:42.485 --> 00:17:45.125
When you're ready. find out
where the father is. Yes. sir.

408
00:17:47.845 --> 00:17:49.765
(MUSIC FADES)

409
00:17:50.165 --> 00:17:51.765
Graphite?
(SIGHS)

410
00:17:52.165 --> 00:17:54.005
Yes. that's right. miss.

411
00:17:54.405 --> 00:17:56.645
Just like they use
in your school pencils.

412
00:17:56.805 --> 00:17:59.365
But the police use it for-
Fingerprints.

413
00:17:59.525 --> 00:18:02.645
And that would be luminol.
used to test for haemoglobin.

414
00:18:03.045 --> 00:18:04.565
Uh. Miss de Luce.

415
00:18:04.725 --> 00:18:07.765
do you think you could find anyone
who might make us a cup of tea?

416
00:18:08.165 --> 00:18:10.405
Do you think you could
manage to rustle something up?

417
00:18:11.285 --> 00:18:13.845
I'll see what can be arranged.
Inspector.

418
00:18:14.085 --> 00:18:15.845
Thank you.

419
00:18:16.645 --> 00:18:18.885
Oh. and we'll come in for it.

420
00:18:18.965 --> 00:18:21.125
No need for you to come out again.

421
00:18:22.965 --> 00:18:24.885
(CURIOUS MUSIC)
So that's how it is.

422
00:18:25.285 --> 00:18:27.685
The only female in sight
is promptly enlisted

423
00:18:27.845 --> 00:18:29.285
to trot off and boil some water.

424
00:18:30.405 --> 00:18:32.805
(CURIOUS MUSIC BECOMES TENSE)

425
00:18:32.965 --> 00:18:34.485
(DOOR SHUTS)
(SIGHS)

426
00:18:34.645 --> 00:18:36.085
Rustle something up...
(MUSIC FADES)

427
00:18:36.485 --> 00:18:38.325
What does he take me for. a cowboy?

428
00:18:38.405 --> 00:18:40.165
VRR
Shouldn't you be at breakfast?

429
00:18:40.485 --> 00:18:42.565
The police are asking for some tea.

430
00:18:42.885 --> 00:18:44.565
But I haven't made any biscuits!

431
00:18:45.445 --> 00:18:47.525
I shouldn't go to any great effort.

432
00:18:49.285 --> 00:18:51.845
(CURIOUS. MAGICAL NOTE)
Biscuits.

433
00:18:52.005 --> 00:18:54.245
Biscuits. there we are.

434
00:18:54.405 --> 00:18:56.965
Oh. four eggs. right.

435
00:18:57.045 --> 00:18:59.685
(CURIOUS MUSIC)

436
00:19:00.485 --> 00:19:02.565
(UTENSILS CLATTERING)
Scoot.

437
00:19:02.645 --> 00:19:04.725
(CURIOUS MUSIC STOPS)

438
00:19:04.885 --> 00:19:06.405
Sorry I'm late.

439
00:19:06.485 --> 00:19:08.085
I had to speak to the police.

440
00:19:09.205 --> 00:19:11.125
About the body.

441
00:19:11.205 --> 00:19:13.125
Which I found in the garden.

442
00:19:14.085 --> 00:19:14.645
ATALE
OF
TWO CITIES

443
00:19:14.965 --> 00:19:17.125
Murdered. most likely.

444
00:19:20.245 --> 00:19:22.165
(SIGHS)

445
00:19:24.725 --> 00:19:26.885
Well. who was it. then?

446
00:19:27.685 --> 00:19:28.965
No idea.

447
00:19:29.125 --> 00:19:30.885
Was there much blood?
Not a drop.

448
00:19:31.045 --> 00:19:32.325
How did he die. then?

449
00:19:32.405 --> 00:19:34.165
My money's on poison. (CRUNCHES)

450
00:19:34.325 --> 00:19:36.245
Perhaps he ate some
of Mrs Mullet's cooking.

451
00:19:36.405 --> 00:19:38.325
Actually.
I noticed a slice of pie missing.

452
00:19:38.725 --> 00:19:40.325
Did either of you eat some?

453
00:19:40.485 --> 00:19:42.885
(SCOFFS)
(LAUGHS)

454
00:19:43.045 --> 00:19:45.125
No. of course not.

455
00:19:46.245 --> 00:19:47.685
Oh.

456
00:19:47.845 --> 00:19:50.245
I beg your pardon. The telephone?

457
00:19:50.645 --> 00:19:52.645
It's in the cupboard
under the stairs. Thank you.

458
00:19:52.805 --> 00:19:54.565
(PLAYFUL RHYTHMIC MUSIC)

459
00:19:55.685 --> 00:19:58.645
extremely athletic individual?

460
00:19:58.965 --> 00:20:00.965
That is Detective Sergeant Graves.

461
00:20:01.125 --> 00:20:04.165
I think- I think I'm just going
to go and change my jumper.

462
00:20:04.405 --> 00:20:06.405
Better put on some lipstick
while you're at it.

463
00:20:06.565 --> 00:20:08.645
You're looking a tad peaky.
(CHUCKLES QUIETLY)

464
00:20:08.805 --> 00:20:10.085
(DOORBELL RINGS)

465
00:20:10.485 --> 00:20:12.805
(BIRDS CHIRPING)
(DOORBELL RINGS REPEATEDLY)

466
00:20:13.685 --> 00:20:16.005
(DOOR CREAKS)
(MUSIC ENDS)

467
00:20:16.085 --> 00:20:17.925
(BIRDS TWEETING)

468
00:20:18.005 --> 00:20:19.285
Coroner.

469
00:20:19.365 --> 00:20:20.885
Flavia.

470
00:20:22.485 --> 00:20:24.485
(CROWS CAWING)

471
00:20:29.205 --> 00:20:32.245
First corpse. always the hardest.

472
00:20:33.365 --> 00:20:34.965
Stays with you the longest.

473
00:20:35.845 --> 00:20:37.365
Morning. Fred.

474
00:20:37.765 --> 00:20:39.285
Morning. Inspector.

475
00:20:40.325 --> 00:20:41.845
Anyone we know?

476
00:20:42.005 --> 00:20:43.525
Doesn't seem like it.

477
00:20:43.605 --> 00:20:46.165
No identification. empty pockets.

478
00:20:46.565 --> 00:20:47.525
Oh.

479
00:20:47.765 --> 00:20:51.045
We do have reason to believe he may
have recently travelled from Norway

480
00:20:51.445 --> 00:20:52.725
Typical. innit?

481
00:20:53.045 --> 00:20:54.245
Bloody Norwegians.

482
00:20:55.045 --> 00:20:56.645
Can't they die at home?

483
00:20:57.685 --> 00:20:59.045
Quite.

484
00:20:59.925 --> 00:21:02.085
Would you care to speculate
on time of death?

485
00:21:02.485 --> 00:21:03.765
(SIGHS) Oof...

486
00:21:04.165 --> 00:21:05.365
Uh..

487
00:21:05.525 --> 00:21:06.885
Have a guess?

488
00:21:06.965 --> 00:21:08.565
Midnight?

489
00:21:08.645 --> 00:21:09.925
Mm-mmm.

490
00:21:10.085 --> 00:21:11.925
(CROW CAWING)
(AWKWARD MUSIC)

491
00:21:12.325 --> 00:21:13.845
Uh... (CLEARS THROAT)

492
00:21:15.925 --> 00:21:18.165
I'm warning you! You step away!
Dogger!

493
00:21:18.325 --> 00:21:20.245
I understand. sir.
I just still need your fingerprints.

494
00:21:20.645 --> 00:21:22.245
(PANTING) Step back.

495
00:21:22.405 --> 00:21:23.925
Steady on. Dogger.

496
00:21:24.005 --> 00:21:25.765
I've got him covered.

497
00:21:25.845 --> 00:21:27.445
Miss de Luce.

498
00:21:27.525 --> 00:21:29.285
Is that you? You're... Don't move.

499
00:21:29.365 --> 00:21:31.125
I'm so sorry.

500
00:21:32.245 --> 00:21:33.925
Is it broken?

501
00:21:34.325 --> 00:21:36.325
I borrowed it yesterday
to cut a bit of twine.

502
00:21:36.485 --> 00:21:38.325
and I might have jammed the blade.

503
00:21:38.725 --> 00:21:40.485
(CROWS CAWING)
(KNIFE FOLDING UP)

504
00:21:40.645 --> 00:21:42.165
Miss de Luce!

505
00:21:42.965 --> 00:21:44.725
A word. if I may.

506
00:21:45.605 --> 00:21:47.605
Who was that man
whon ou wer e just speaking?

507
00:21:47.765 --> 00:21:48.965
Dogger.

508
