(SIGHS DEEPLY)

1013
00:44:31.365 --> 00:44:33.605
I overheard your quarrel
with Bonepenny.

1014
00:44:34.565 --> 00:44:36.165
I know he was trying
to blackmail you.

1015
00:44:36.325 --> 00:44:38.565
That's why I told the inspector
that I killed him.

1016
00:44:38.965 --> 00:44:39.765
You what?!

1017
00:44:40.085 --> 00:44:41.845
They can't hang me. you see.

1018
00:44:42.245 --> 00:44:45.125
I want you to know
I don't blame you for what you did.

1019
00:44:45.525 --> 00:44:48.885
I'm sure he was a dreadful man
and fully deserved to die.

1020
00:44:49.765 --> 00:44:51.525
Do you really think

1021
00:44:52.405 --> 00:44:54.565
that your father
is capable of murder?

1022
00:44:54.725 --> 00:44:59.125
Then why did Bonepenny say that you
killed your teacher. Mr Teesdale?

1023
00:44:59.285 --> 00:45:00.965
(INHALES)

1024
00:45:03.765 --> 00:45:05.525
(CLICKS TONGUE)

1025
00:45:05.605 --> 00:45:08.405
I was a solitary lad at school.

1026
00:45:09.525 --> 00:45:11.205
Unbearably homesick.

1027
00:45:11.605 --> 00:45:14.725
(GENTLE. CURIOUS MUSIC)
(INDISTINCT CHATTER AND LAUGHTER)

1028
00:45:14.885 --> 00:45:17.205
If it hadn't been for
our Latin master. Mr Teesdale.

1029
00:45:17.605 --> 00:45:20.005
I... don't know
if I would've survived.

1030
00:45:20.885 --> 00:45:23.925
He founded the Magic Circle Club

1031
00:45:24.085 --> 00:45:26.325
as a way of helping
those boys who didn't fit in.

1032
00:45:26.725 --> 00:45:27.445
(SIGHS)

1033
00:45:27.605 --> 00:45:29.685
Well done. Jacko.
(APPLAUSE)

1034
00:45:29.765 --> 00:45:31.125
Who's next?

1035
00:45:31.525 --> 00:45:34.405
'It was there that I first met
Horace Bonepenny.

1036
00:45:34.485 --> 00:45:36.565
He was even more of a misfit
than I was.

1037
00:45:36.725 --> 00:45:38.805
Bony was a... natural conjurer.

1038
00:45:38.965 --> 00:45:40.805
(APPLAUSE)
'The French Drop.

1039
00:45:41.685 --> 00:45:44.645
The Haunted Handkerchief.'
(CURIOUS MUSIC CONTINUES)

1040
00:45:44.805 --> 00:45:47.205
(EXCLAMATIONS. CHUCKLING. APPLAUS

1041
00:45:47.605 --> 00:45:49.125
'The Ghost Light.'
(POOF)

1042
00:45:49.365 --> 00:45:50.565
ALL: Woah!
Well done!

1043
00:45:50.965 --> 00:45:52.005
(APPLAUSE)
'He knew them all.'

1044
00:45:52.405 --> 00:45:53.365
You were a conjurer?

1045
00:45:53.765 --> 00:45:55.285
No. no. no. no.
That was Horace's passion.

1046
00:45:55.445 --> 00:45:58.005
Mine was for something
far more exciting.

1047
00:45:59.525 --> 00:46:01.285
Stamp collecting.

1048
00:46:01.605 --> 00:46:03.285
(SIGHS)

1049
00:46:03.365 --> 00:46:05.365
Another of Teesdale's passions.

1050
00:46:05.445 --> 00:46:06.725
Penny Black.

1051
00:46:07.045 --> 00:46:08.485
In perforate.

1052
00:46:08.645 --> 00:46:10.645
1841. I would guess.

1053
00:46:11.045 --> 00:46:14.245
'But there was one other master at
Greyminster who could outmatch it.

1054
00:46:14.645 --> 00:46:17.445
Our headmaster. Dr Kissing.'
There. There. You see?

1055
00:46:17.845 --> 00:46:20.565
'Most of Kissing's collection
was fairly run-of-the-mill.

1056
00:46:20.725 --> 00:46:23.205
except for one stamp.
(EXCLAMATIONS)

1057
00:46:23.605 --> 00:46:26.165
One stamp of inestimable value.

1058
00:46:27.045 --> 00:46:30.005
It was our most fervent desire
to get a glimpse of that stamp.

1059
00:46:30.085 --> 00:46:31.605
And then...

1060
00:46:32.485 --> 00:46:34.245
..one fateful night..

1061
00:46:34.565 --> 00:46:36.565
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

1062
00:46:36.725 --> 00:46:38.885
(SOUND DISTORTS)

1063
00:46:40.245 --> 00:46:42.485
(MECHANISM CLANKING. ECHOES)

1064
00:46:43.525 --> 00:46:45.445
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

1065
00:46:47.125 --> 00:46:48.805
(MUSIC STOPS)
By this time.

1066
00:46:49.205 --> 00:46:52.645
Bonepenny had found a...
new friend and accomplice.

1067
00:46:52.805 --> 00:46:54.405
(WHISPERING)
'An older boy named Bob Stanley

1068
00:46:54.805 --> 00:46:56.325
with whom he'd begun to
spend all his time.

1069
00:46:57.205 --> 00:46:59.365
Hello. Bony. Bob.

1070
00:46:59.445 --> 00:47:01.365
(MIMICS) Hello. Bony. Bob.
(SNORTS)

1071
00:47:01.765 --> 00:47:03.605
Now. as I told you before.

1072
00:47:03.765 --> 00:47:06.405
my grandfather was a partner
in the firm PKP.

1073
00:47:06.805 --> 00:47:09.045
Perkins. Kissing and Petch.
(CURIOUS MUSIC)

1074
00:47:09.445 --> 00:47:13.285
Sole printers of British postage
stamps at the time of Queen Victoria.

1075
00:47:14.165 --> 00:47:17.605
Now. in 1841. a terrorist group

1076
00:47:17.685 --> 00:47:20.885
managed to ink a set of orange stamps

1077
00:47:21.285 --> 00:47:26.645
with the aim of igniting a violent
uprising against the queen.

1078
00:47:26.805 --> 00:47:28.645
Now. this was at a time

1079
00:47:29.045 --> 00:47:31.525
when a mere stamp could
inspire a revolution.

1080
00:47:31.925 --> 00:47:33.685
(ALL MURMURING)
The plot was uncovered.

1081
00:47:33.845 --> 00:47:36.085
and the stamps destroyed.

1082
00:47:36.885 --> 00:47:39.525
All except one.

1083
00:47:39.685 --> 00:47:43.525
AA.
which was reserved for Queen Victoria

1084
00:47:43.685 --> 00:47:46.325
as a memento of her
escape from death.

1085
00:47:47.685 --> 00:47:51.205
However. there was another stamp.

1086
00:47:51.605 --> 00:47:54.485
TL. from the opposite corner.

1087
00:47:54.645 --> 00:47:58.245
which my grandfather
secretly kept for himself.

1088
00:47:58.645 --> 00:48:00.805
a stamp of priceless value...
(ALL MURMURING)

1089
00:48:01.205 --> 00:48:03.045
..which my grandfather
left to my father.

1090
00:48:03.205 --> 00:48:05.445
and my father left to me.
There. you see?

1091
00:48:05.925 --> 00:48:07.285
(TWEEZERS CLACK)
(ALL GASP) Bonepenny!

1092
00:48:07.685 --> 00:48:09.685
Ashes to ashes. dust to dust.
(MUSIC BECOMES DRAMATIC)

1093
00:48:09.845 --> 00:48:11.525
If the king can't have you..
(ALL YELLING)

1094
00:48:11.925 --> 00:48:13.285
.the devil must!
What are you doing?

1095
00:48:13.525 --> 00:48:14.725
(ALL GASP)

1096
00:48:15.045 --> 00:48:16.085
(SIGHS)

1097
00:48:16.405 --> 00:48:17.765
(WHISPERS) What- What have you done

1098
00:48:18.085 --> 00:48:19.605
Bonepenny. what have you done?

1099
00:48:19.765 --> 00:48:21.685
It's OK. sir. It's just a trick.

1100
00:48:21.845 --> 00:48:23.605
Now. all of you need to help
me to get it back.

1101
00:48:24.005 --> 00:48:25.125
If we all join hands and pray...

1102
00:48:25.525 --> 00:48:26.805
Come on. Jacko. And you. Bob.

1103
00:48:26.885 --> 00:48:28.165
It's not funny. Bony.

1104
00:48:28.565 --> 00:48:29.845
Just join hands and form a circle.

1105
00:48:30.005 --> 00:48:31.685
Enough of this insolence. Hmm?

1106
00:48:32.085 --> 00:48:33.605
Put the stamp back.
But. sir!

1107
00:48:34.005 --> 00:48:35.285
Put the stamp back.

1108
00:48:35.605 --> 00:48:37.445
(TENSE MUSIC)

1109
00:48:37.845 --> 00:48:39.365
(INHALES) Alright.

1110
00:48:40.405 --> 00:48:41.925
I'll have to go at it myself.

1111
00:48:42.885 --> 00:48:44.885
Come back. come back.
oh. Orange Queen.

1112
00:48:45.045 --> 00:48:47.045
Come and show us where you've been
(DRAMATIC NOTE)

1113
00:48:48.485 --> 00:48:50.005
(MURMURS OF RELIEF)
Ah!

1114
00:48:50.165 --> 00:48:52.325
There. You see?

1115
00:48:58.005 --> 00:49:00.245
But this isn't the Avenger.

1116
00:49:00.405 --> 00:49:02.005
BOY: What?
What?

1117
00:49:02.325 --> 00:49:04.885
It's a Canada one cent.
What?

1118
00:49:05.045 --> 00:49:07.045
I'm... sorry. sir. I must've...

1119
00:49:07.205 --> 00:49:08.965
(TENSE MUSIC)

1120
00:49:09.365 --> 00:49:11.045
Where's the stamp?

1121
00:49:11.365 --> 00:49:12.805
Where is the stamp?!

1122
00:49:13.205 --> 00:49:15.685
I'm sorry. sir.
It's worked before lots of times.

1123
00:49:15.845 --> 00:49:18.245
(OMINOUS NOTE)
(SIGHS)

1124
00:49:19.765 --> 00:49:21.605
You wretched boy.

1125
00:49:21.925 --> 00:49:23.445
Get out.

1126
00:49:23.605 --> 00:49:25.525
Get out. Go on. Go to bed!

1127
00:49:25.605 --> 00:49:27.285
(YELLS) All of you. get out!

1128
00:49:28.405 --> 00:49:29.685
I'm so sorry. Jacko.

1129
00:49:30.085 --> 00:49:31.765
It's not me
you should be apologising to.

1130
00:49:32.165 --> 00:49:33.685
(DOOR OPENS)

1131
00:49:35.765 --> 00:49:37.445
Teesdale?

1132
00:49:37.525 --> 00:49:38.805
Headmaster. I- I

1133
00:49:38.885 --> 00:49:41.045
They will have to be punished.
All of them.

1134
00:49:41.205 --> 00:49:43.045
(SOMBRE MUSIC)

1135
00:49:46.725 --> 00:49:48.885
'The caning didn't hurt
nearly so much

1136
00:49:49.045 --> 00:49:51.285
as the sight
of Mr Teesdale's distress.'

1137
00:49:52.165 --> 00:49:54.165
(BLOWS LANDING)

1138
00:49:55.285 --> 00:49:57.285
(FINAL BLOW ECHOES)
He felt...

1139
00:49:57.445 --> 00:49:59.125
..responsible. you see.

1140
00:50:00.725 --> 00:50:03.205
And then. the very next day...

1141
00:50:03.285 --> 00:50:05.765
Look! Up there! On the tower!

1142
00:50:06.085 --> 00:50:07.765
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

1143
00:50:07.925 --> 00:50:09.365
Isay..

1144
00:50:09.445 --> 00:50:10.965
is that Mr Teesdale?

1145
00:50:11.125 --> 00:50:14.165
'He looked like a prophet
from an old manuscript.

1146
00:50:14.325 --> 00:50:16.245
(SHOUTS) Vale!

1147
00:50:16.325 --> 00:50:17.365
(AIR WHOOSHING)

1148
00:50:17.685 --> 00:50:20.165
(LOUD. DRAMATIC NOTES)

1149
00:50:20.325 --> 00:50:22.005
(THUNDER CRASHING)

1150
00:50:22.325 --> 00:50:24.085
It was murder.

1151
00:50:24.165 --> 00:50:26.485
Horace Bonepenny and I murdered him

1152
00:50:26.645 --> 00:50:28.965
as surely as if we had flung him
from the tower with our own hands.

1153
00:50:29.365 --> 00:50:30.885
But you had nothing to do with it!

1154
00:50:31.205 --> 00:50:33.285
He was just a dear. good man.

1155
00:50:33.445 --> 00:50:35.285
an innocent dupe.

1156
00:50:35.365 --> 00:50:37.605
When I returned to my room.

1157
00:50:38.005 --> 00:50:41.285
I found a strange.
uh. sticky spot on my sleeve.

1158
00:50:41.445 --> 00:50:44.245
I realised immediately
what had happened.

1159
00:50:44.485 --> 00:50:48.485
Bonepenny hadn't
destroyed the stamp.

1160
00:50:48.565 --> 00:50:50.485
He had stuck it onto my cuff.

1161
00:50:50.885 --> 00:50:53.445
and then retrieved it later
when he shook my hand.

1162
00:50:53.605 --> 00:50:54.885
And I...

1163
00:50:55.285 --> 00:50:56.485
said...

1164
00:50:57.605 --> 00:50:59.205
(WHISPERS) ..nothing.

1165
00:50:59.605 --> 00:51:01.765
(CURIOUS MUSIC)
Schoolboy's honour.

1166
00:51:01.925 --> 00:51:03.685
And all that rot.

1167
00:51:04.005 --> 00:51:05.685
What happened to Bonepenny?

1168
00:51:06.005 --> 00:51:07.845
He left shortly afterwards.

1169
00:51:08.005 --> 00:51:09.525
And Stanley?

1170
00:51:09.605 --> 00:51:11.125
He left too.

1171
00:51:11.525 --> 00:51:14.965
I heard that he had died when
his ship was torpedoed in the war.

1172
00:51:15.045 --> 00:51:17.685
I hadn't thought of either of them
in years.

1173
00:51:17.845 --> 00:51:20.485
And then last week
at the exhibition..

1174
00:51:20.645 --> 00:51:22.245
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1175
00:51:22.405 --> 00:51:26.005
'I was studying some items
from the king's collection.

1176
00:51:27.125 --> 00:51:29.525
(WHISPERS) And there it was.

1177
00:51:29.605 --> 00:51:30.485
[AONEDENNYA]

1178
00:51:30.485 --> 00:51:32.565
AONEPENNYA
AA.

1179
00:51:33.765 --> 00:51:35.365
The twin

1180
00:51:35.685 --> 00:51:37.205
of Kissing's stamp.

1181
00:51:39.045 --> 00:51:41.445
I thought I had imagined
Bonepenny. but...

1182
00:51:42.325 --> 00:51:44.645
(LOW. TENSE MUSIC)

1183
00:51:44.965 --> 00:51:46.245
(SMASHING)

1184
00:51:48.965 --> 00:51:50.965
Bonepenny stole the king's stamp!

1185
00:51:51.125 --> 00:51:53.685
When the jack snipe appeared
on our doorstep.

1186
00:51:54.565 --> 00:51:56.165
I knew he was coming.

1187
00:51:56.565 --> 00:51:59.605
Jack Snipe was my nickname at
school. or Jacko for short.

1188
00:51:59.765 --> 00:52:01.365
The bird was a warning. you see.

1189
00:52:01.685 --> 00:52:03.925
But why? What did he want from you?

1190
00:52:04.245 --> 00:52:05.765
Blackmail.

1191
00:52:06.645 --> 00:52:08.885
The stamps
were too notorious to sell.

1192
00:52:09.765 --> 00:52:11.845
and so he wanted me to buy them.

1193
00:52:12.005 --> 00:52:15.125
threatening to frame me
for both thefts if I didn't.

1194
00:52:16.085 --> 00:52:18.485
He had it all planned out
to the last detail.

1195
00:52:18.645 --> 00:52:20.485
like one of his magic tricks.

1196
00:52:20.645 --> 00:52:22.325
What did you tell him?
The truth.

1197
00:52:22.725 --> 00:52:24.805
That I haven't any money. (CHUCKLES)

1198
00:52:24.885 --> 00:52:26.645
It's all tied up in taxes.

1199
00:52:28.005 --> 00:52:31.045
I may have to sell Buckshaw.
What?!

1200
00:52:31.445 --> 00:52:33.685
But surely you heard all that
when you were listening at the door?

1201
00:52:34.085 --> 00:52:36.245
I didn't hear that part!
Dogger intercepted me.

1202
00:52:37.685 --> 00:52:39.285
Dogger was there?

1203
00:52:39.605 --> 00:52:40.885
Yes.

1204
00:52:43.445 --> 00:52:45.125
That is what I feared the most.

1205
00:52:46.005 --> 00:52:48.165
That he would think I was in danger.

1206
00:52:48.325 --> 00:52:50.405
That he would.
(THUD. LOCK CLICKING)

1207
00:52:51.285 --> 00:52:53.205
(DOOR CREAKING)

1208
00:52:53.605 --> 00:52:55.605
Time's up. I'm afraid.
Please. Inspector.

1209
00:52:55.765 --> 00:52:58.005
Just 5 more minutes.
I'm sorry. Flavia.

1210
00:53:00.485 --> 00:53:02.005
(INHALES)

1211
00:53:02.085 --> 00:53:03.365
Vale.

1212
00:53:03.525 --> 00:53:05.125
(SOMBRE MUSIC)
(SNIFFLES)

1213
00:53:06.005 --> 00:53:08.405
(INHALES)
Oh!

1214
00:53:08.565 --> 00:53:10.005
(SIGHS)

1215
00:53:10.885 --> 00:53:13.045
SOMBRE MUSIC CONTINUES)

1216
00:53:15.365 --> 00:53:17.365
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

1217
00:53:18.245 --> 00:53:20.405
(INHALES SHAKILY) Alright.
(GASPS SOFTLY)

1218
00:53:21.285 --> 00:53:22.725
(SOFTLY) Flavia...

1219
00:53:23.125 --> 00:53:25.525
Flavia. Flavia!
(SIGHS)

1220
00:53:25.925 --> 00:53:27.765
Courage. my dear.

1221
00:53:27.845 --> 00:53:30.165
(SHAKY BREATHS)

1222
00:53:31.285 --> 00:53:33.285
(DISTANT MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTL

1223
00:53:33.685 --> 00:53:35.605
(SOMBRE MUSIC CONTINUES)

1224
00:53:38.245 --> 00:53:40.245
Uh. in- inspector?

1225
00:53:41.765 --> 00:53:43.285
A word?

1226
00:53:45.125 --> 00:53:47.525
(RAINFALL)
(SOMBRE MUSIC CONTINUES)

1227
00:53:52.005 --> 00:53:55.125
His name was Horace Bonepenny.

1228
00:53:56.165 --> 00:53:58.085
Yes. Thank you.

1229
00:53:58.965 --> 00:54:01.365
I was j just speaking to
Scotland Yard.

1230
00:54:01.525 --> 00:54:04.645
Apparently. Bonepenny
is a very well-known con man.

1231
00:54:05.285 --> 00:54:07.605
Why won't you believe I killed him?

1232
00:54:07.765 --> 00:54:09.365
Clever as you are. Flavia.

1233
00:54:09.845 --> 00:54:11.845
I don't believe
you're capable of murder.

1234
00:54:12.965 --> 00:54:15.605
And it wasn't a dicky heart
that killed Bonepenny.

1235
00:54:16.005 --> 00:54:17.445
(INHALES) The pie. then.

1236
00:54:18.245 --> 00:54:20.245
I poisoned it. and he ate it.

1237
00:54:20.485 --> 00:54:23.685
According to the report.
it was a perfectly ordinary pie.

1238
00:54:23.845 --> 00:54:26.965
You've obviously never tasted
one of Mrs Mullet's custards.

1239
00:54:27.205 --> 00:54:29.045
(INHALES SHAKILY)
It's all so unfair!

1240
00:54:29.445 --> 00:54:32.085
You haven't got a shred of evidence
against my father.

1241
00:54:32.485 --> 00:54:34.005
I'm sorry. Flavia.

1242
00:54:34.405 --> 00:54:36.645
but your father
has just confessed to murder.

1243
00:54:36.805 --> 00:54:38.885
(SOMBRE MUSIC)

1244
00:54:43.045 --> 00:54:43.605
KFF

1245
00:54:44.005 --> 00:54:44.325

1246
1244
00:55:02.965 --> 00:55:05.205
(SOMBRE MUSIC CONTINUES)

1247
00:55:14.485 --> 00:55:17.045
Mrs Mullet. may I speak frankly?

1248
00:55:17.285 --> 00:55:18.805
(MUSIC FADES)
It's about Dogger.

1249
00:55:19.205 --> 00:55:21.445
About when he was
a prisoner in the war.

1250
00:55:22.325 --> 00:55:25.765
(SLOwLY) Did Dogger ever kill anyone?

1251
00:55:26.645 --> 00:55:28.965
I mean. besides the enemy.

1252
00:55:30.565 --> 00:55:32.245
our father.. (SIGHS)

1253
00:55:33.045 --> 00:55:34.565
..saved his life once.

1254
00:55:34.965 --> 00:55:36.725
Pulled him out of a burning tank.

1255
00:55:38.965 --> 00:55:41.605
Then Dogger did the same for him.

1256
00:55:42.725 --> 00:55:44.885
An army bloke went off his head.

1257
00:55:45.125 --> 00:55:47.605
tried to kill the colonel
with a machete.

1258
00:55:49.925 --> 00:55:51.445
Dogger...

1259
00:55:53.125 --> 00:55:54.645
..took care of it.

1260
00:55:56.565 --> 00:55:58.725
Afterwards.
he couldn't remember a thing.

1261
00:55:58.805 --> 00:56:02.485
It was the start of his spells.
you see.

1262
00:56:04.165 --> 00:56:06.165
The things that happened
over there...

1263
00:56:07.285 --> 00:56:08.725
No man should ever..

1264
00:56:11.605 --> 00:56:13.445
(INHALES SHARPLY) Not juSt men.

1265
00:56:14.565 --> 00:56:16.325
Your mother.

1266
00:56:17.925 --> 00:56:19.285
Harriet?

1267
00:56:19.605 --> 00:56:21.125
(SNIFFLES)

1268
00:56:22.005 --> 00:56:23.445
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

1269
00:56:23.525 --> 00:56:25.125
Did you know her?

1270
00:56:26.485 --> 00:56:28.885
I worked with your mother
during the war

1271
00:56:29.045 --> 00:56:30.485
Very hush-hush.

1272
00:56:31.605 --> 00:56:33.685
After your mother left...

1273
00:56:36.245 --> 00:56:38.565
(INHALES DEEPLY) I waS Sent here.

1274
00:56:38.725 --> 00:56:41.125
Didn't know the first thing
about housekeeping.

1275
00:56:41.525 --> 00:56:44.485
(CHUCKLES) Thank goodness for this.

1276
00:56:47.285 --> 00:56:49.765
Mrs Mullet. what is...

1277
00:56:50.645 --> 00:56:52.245
..The Nest?

1278
00:56:53.445 --> 00:56:55.285
Drink up now.
(MUG THUDS)

1279
00:56:55.445 --> 00:56:57.045
And straight to bed.

1280
00:56:57.845 --> 00:57:00.805
(CURIOUS MUSIC FADES IN)

1281
00:57:10.645 --> 00:57:11.205
THING

1282
00:57:12.805 --> 00:57:14.485
(GASPS)

1283
00:57:15.525 --> 00:57:17.445
(TENSE MUSIC)

1284
00:57:23.205 --> 00:57:24.805
(SIGHS)

1285
00:57:28.245 --> 00:57:30.325
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

1286
00:57:30.725 --> 00:57:33.125
FATHER (ECHOES):
'He was just an innocent dupe.'

1287
00:57:33.285 --> 00:57:34.725
(SIGHS)

1288
00:57:35.125 --> 00:57:37.125
MOUNT JOY (ECHOES):
'He was murdered..

1289
00:57:37.525 --> 00:57:39.605
by those two boys.'

1290
00:57:40.005 --> 00:57:42.405
(INHALES DEEPLY)
It just doesn't add up.

1291
00:57:42.805 --> 00:57:44.005
(YELLS) Vale!

1292
00:57:44.165 --> 00:57:46.965
(SHOUTING)

1293
00:57:47.045 --> 00:57:49.605
(GASPS LOUDLY. PANTING)

1294
00:57:50.725 --> 00:57:53.045
(EXCITING MUSIC)
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

1295
00:57:56.085 --> 00:57:58.885
(DISTANT MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

1296
00:58:03.365 --> 00:58:05.285
(MUSIC LULLS)

1297
00:58:06.645 --> 00:58:08.965
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

1298
00:58:09.125 --> 00:58:11.285
(LOW. MISCHIEVOUS MUSIC)

1299
00:58:13.205 --> 00:58:15.205
(MUSIC BUILDS. CONCLUDES)

1300
00:58:15.285 --> 00:58:17.045
(FLOOR CREAKING)

1301
00:58:18.405 --> 00:58:20.405
Is that Rook's End Nursing Home?

1302
00:58:20.725 --> 00:58:22.405
I'd like to speak to Dr Kissing.

1303
00:58:22.485 --> 00:58:24.005
(CURIOUS MUSIC)

1304
00:58:24.405 --> 00:58:27.045
It's Mrs Rubbles
from Greyminster School.

1305
00:58:27.205 --> 00:58:30.405
calling to ask whether he'll be
coming for Prize Day this year.

1306
00:58:30.725 --> 00:58:32.405
(WHISPERS) Dr Kissing?

1307
00:58:32.485 --> 00:58:34.245
He's still alive.

1308
00:58:34.325 --> 00:58:36.245
(TYPEWRITER KEYS CLACKING)

1309
00:58:37.845 --> 00:58:40.325
(CURIOUS MUSIC CONTINUES)

1310
00:58:40.645 --> 00:58:42.485
(HINGES CREAKING)

1311
00:58:42.565 --> 00:58:44.085
(PIGEONS COOING)

1312
00:58:44.405 --> 00:58:45.685
(SIGHS)

1313
00:58:46.565 --> 00:58:48.645
(MUSIC BECOMES DRAMATIC)

1314
00:58:52.165 --> 00:58:53.845
(DRAMATIC MUSIC LULLS)

1315
00:58:55.205 --> 00:58:57.205
(WIND GUSTING)
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

1316
00:58:59.205 --> 00:59:01.045
(METAL CLINKING)

1317
00:59:02.725 --> 00:59:04.725
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1318
00:59:07.285 --> 00:59:10.245
(ECHOES) '"Said one of the boys.
He climbed up onto the parapet.

1319
00:59:10.645 --> 00:59:13.285
gave us the Roman salute.
'Vale! he shouted."

1320
00:59:13.445 --> 00:59:15.365
(SIGHS)

1321
00:59:18.085 --> 00:59:19.685
(GRUNTS)

1322
00:59:19.845 --> 00:59:21.525
(DISTANT LAUGHTER & CHATTER)

1323
00:59:22.645 --> 00:59:25.765
(SIGHS)
(BELL RINGING)

1324
00:59:26.885 --> 00:59:28.725
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1325
00:59:29.525 --> 00:59:30.965
Huh...

1326
00:59:32.645 --> 00:59:33.765
(YELPS. SCREAMS)

1327
00:59:33.925 --> 00:59:35.445
(ROPE WHOOSHING)
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

1328
00:59:35.845 --> 00:59:37.205
(SHRIEKS)

1329
00:59:38.725 --> 00:59:40.085
(POLE CREAKS)
(SCREAMS)

1330
00:59:40.165 --> 00:59:41.365
(GRUNTS) Argh!

1331
00:59:41.765 --> 00:59:44.245
(BELL CONTINUES RINGING)
BOY: What was that?

1332
00:59:44.405 --> 00:59:46.645
Did you hear that?

1333
00:59:46.805 --> 00:59:48.005
(GASPS. PANTING)

1334
00:59:48.165 --> 00:59:49.845
Blast.

1335
00:59:50.005 --> 00:59:51.685
(PANTING. SIGHS)

1336
00:59:51.845 --> 00:59:53.605
(WIND GUSTING)

1337
00:59:54.005 --> 00:59:55.925
What have we here?
(CURIOUS MUSIC)

1338
00:59:57.365 --> 00:59:58.645
A gown.

1339
00:59:59.445 --> 01:00:01.125
(SNIFFS)

1340
01:00:01.205 --> 01:00:02.485
Eurgh...

1341
01:00:06.965 --> 01:00:09.125
(GASPS SOFTLY) And a mortarboard!

1342
01:00:09.205 --> 01:00:11.525
(MUSIC BUILDS SLOWLY)

1343
01:00:11.685 --> 01:00:13.365
(EXCITING MUSIC)
(BIKE BELL RINGS)

1344
01:00:14.725 --> 01:00:16.565
(GEAR WHIRRING)

1345
01:00:16.885 --> 01:00:18.245
Woohoo!

1346
01:00:18.325 --> 01:00:21.605
Fly. Gladys. fly! Woo!

1347
01:00:21.925 --> 01:00:23.205
(MUSIC CONCLUDES)

1348
01:00:24.405 --> 01:00:26.725
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)
What's the password?

1349
01:00:26.885 --> 01:00:28.485
DOGGER: Cyanide.

1350
01:00:30.485 --> 01:00:32.565
(HINGES SQUEAK)

1351
01:00:32.885 --> 01:00:34.885
Dogger. what is it?
(SIGHS)

1352
01:00:35.045 --> 01:00:38.405
Miss Flavia.
you know I have moments when

1353
01:00:39.285 --> 01:00:40.885
..not quite myself?

1354
01:00:41.285 --> 01:00:43.925
I had one of those moments
on the night we...

1355
01:00:44.885 --> 01:00:48.085
And now they've charged
Colonel de Luce with it.

1356
01:00:48.245 --> 01:00:50.325
(SIGHS)

1357
01:00:50.325 --> 01:00:52.005
(SIGHS)
(SIGHS)

1358
01:00:52.885 --> 01:00:54.325
Dogger.

1359
01:00:54.725 --> 01:00:56.085
Tell me everything you remember

1360
01:00:56.485 --> 01:00:59.045
about the night
that the stranger was killed.

1361
01:00:59.205 --> 01:01:00.885
(INHALES) I waS in my

1362
01:01:01.685 --> 01:01:03.205
I heard voices.

1363
01:01:03.525 --> 01:01:06.005
I went along to the Colonel's study.

1364
01:01:06.165 --> 01:01:08.805
(TENSE PIANO MUSIC)
There was someone in the hall.

1365
01:01:09.685 --> 01:01:11.845
That was me. I was in the hall.

1366
01:01:12.245 --> 01:01:13.525
That was you?

1367
01:01:13.845 --> 01:01:15.125
No matter.

1368
01:01:15.925 --> 01:01:17.525
What happened after I left?

1369
01:01:18.645 --> 01:01:21.685
A man came out.
and he walked right past me.

1370
01:01:22.085 --> 01:01:23.765
I could've reached out
and touched him.

1371
01:01:24.165 --> 01:01:27.125
He was talking to himself and...
eating a piece of pie.

1372
01:01:28.005 --> 01:01:29.605
I knew it wasn't one of us!

1373
01:01:30.725 --> 01:01:32.245
Then what?

1374
01:01:32.645 --> 01:01:34.085
(THUD)
(FIREWORKS EXPLODING)

1375
01:01:34.245 --> 01:01:35.765
Fireworks.

1376
01:01:36.085 --> 01:01:37.365
Fireworks?

1377
01:01:37.525 --> 01:01:39.445
Catherine wheels. skyrockets.

1378
01:01:39.525 --> 01:01:41.605
There must've been a fair in town.
(THUD)

1379
01:01:41.765 --> 01:01:43.045
There was no fair in town.

1380
01:01:43.445 --> 01:01:45.045
Are you sure?
Trust me.

1381
01:01:45.205 --> 01:01:47.445
I'm 11. I know when the fairs are.

1382
01:01:47.765 --> 01:01:49.205
What happened next?

1383
01:01:49.525 --> 01:01:51.765
I fell asleep.

1384
01:01:52.085 --> 01:01:52.885
(GASPS)

1385
01:01:53.285 --> 01:01:54.725
'When I woke up.
I was on the grass.'

1386
01:01:55.045 --> 01:01:56.485
(GROANS)
'It was wet.

1387
01:01:56.565 --> 01:01:58.725
And my head felt strange...
(SIGHS)

1388
01:01:58.885 --> 01:02:01.125
'..like it does
after one of my bad turns.

1389
01:02:01.525 --> 01:02:02.885
And you're worried that...

1390
01:02:03.205 --> 01:02:04.725
during your bad turn.

1391
01:02:05.125 --> 01:02:06.725
you might've killed the stranger?

1392
01:02:07.845 --> 01:02:09.365
Who else was there?

1393
01:02:10.485 --> 01:02:12.085
(SCREAMS)

1394
01:02:14.725 --> 01:02:16.405
(CRYING)

1395
01:02:16.565 --> 01:02:18.805
Feely! Speak to me. darling.

1396
01:02:19.205 --> 01:02:21.525
What's wrong?
It's too ghastly for words.

1397
01:02:21.685 --> 01:02:23.845
(CR YING)
(CURIOUS MUSIC)

1398
01:02:24.085 --> 01:02:26.325
Uh..
(CRYING CONTINUES)

1399
01:02:26.725 --> 01:02:28.325
(SNIFFLES)

1400
01:02:29.685 --> 01:02:32.325
(EXHALES)
I'll get some calamine lotion.

1401
01:02:32.725 --> 01:02:34.085
(CRYING)

1402
01:02:34.485 --> 01:02:37.125
You might want to start digging
that second grave. miss. (GASPS)

1403
01:02:37.285 --> 01:02:39.365
(CR YING CONTINUES)

1404
01:02:39.525 --> 01:02:41.125
(WINCES)
(MUSIC CONCLUDES)

1405
01:02:42.245 --> 01:02:45.205
Feely. eat something. darling.

1406
01:02:45.285 --> 01:02:47.925
can't. It hurts too much.

1407
01:02:48.085 --> 01:02:49.605
Just a little porridge?

1408
01:02:50.965 --> 01:02:52.485
Feely...

1409
01:02:53.605 --> 01:02:55.125
I'm so sorry.

1410
01:02:55.205 --> 01:02:56.885
What are YoU sorry for?

1411
01:02:58.805 --> 01:03:00.885
(INHALES) I...

1412
01:03:01.205 --> 01:03:02.485
(EXHALES)

1413
01:03:02.645 --> 01:03:04.725
It looks very painful.

1414
01:03:05.125 --> 01:03:07.685
(KNOCKING)
Good God! Who is that?

1415
01:03:07.845 --> 01:03:09.605
It's alright. I know him.

1416
01:03:09.685 --> 01:03:11.365
That's hard eassuring.

1417
01:03:13.845 --> 01:03:16.005
(BIRDS CHIRPING)
Good morning. Flavia!

1418
01:03:16.165 --> 01:03:19.045
(SNEEZES)
Oh. dear. Hay fever?

1419
01:03:19.925 --> 01:03:21.445
A cold. I'm afraid.

1420
01:03:22.325 --> 01:03:24.485
What can I help you with.
Mr Pemberton?

1421
01:03:24.645 --> 01:03:28.485
I found something in the local
archives that got my blood pounding.

1422
01:03:28.645 --> 01:03:30.165
Did you know that Buckshaw's
Buried Lake

1423
01:03:30.565 --> 01:03:32.565
was designed by Capability Brown?
Yes!

1424
01:03:33.045 --> 01:03:36.245
The plans are in Father's study.
actually. Oh. my.

1425
01:03:36.405 --> 01:03:39.125
Do you think I could just take
a quick photo of them?

1426
01:03:39.205 --> 01:03:40.885
Maybe with the three of you.
Erm..

1427
01:03:41.045 --> 01:03:42.325
It would be a real feather in my cap

1428
01:03:42.485 --> 01:03:44.165
with the
Inland Waterways Federation.

1429
01:03:44.325 --> 01:03:46.725
There's Dogger. I could ask him.

1430
01:03:47.125 --> 01:03:50.005
Oh. no. no. Don't-
Don't bother a working man. Hello!

1431
01:03:50.165 --> 01:03:52.165
No. it was just a thought.

1432
01:03:52.325 --> 01:03:53.605
Thank you. Flavia.

1433
01:03:54.005 --> 01:03:55.765
It was good to meet you.
We'll meet again sometime.

1434
01:03:56.165 --> 01:03:58.085
A visitor. Miss Flavia?

1435
01:03:58.165 --> 01:03:59.845
His name is Pemberton.

1436
01:03:59.925 --> 01:04:01.605
He's a gongoozler.

1437
01:04:01.765 --> 01:04:03.845
He wanted to see the blueprints
of the buried lake.

1438
01:04:05.605 --> 01:04:07.685
You're quite sure that's what
he's interested in?

1439
01:04:07.765 --> 01:04:09.045
What do you mean?

1440
01:04:09.205 --> 01:04:11.045
There's a certain type of person.

1441
01:04:11.205 --> 01:04:13.365
tabloid hacks. smear merchants.

1442
01:04:13.525 --> 01:04:15.765
scandal mongers.
so-called journalists.

1443
01:04:15.925 --> 01:04:17.685
that will do anything for a story...

1444
01:04:17.845 --> 01:04:20.485
especially when
there's a murder involved.

1445
01:04:20.885 --> 01:04:22.965
I... didn't think of that.

1446
01:04:23.765 --> 01:04:25.365
Speaking of which.

1447
01:04:25.765 --> 01:04:27.285
the inspector rang earlier.

1448
01:04:28.165 --> 01:04:30.645
They're moving the Colonel
to London tomorrow.

1449
01:04:31.045 --> 01:04:32.085
London?
Mmm.

1450
01:04:32.165 --> 01:04:33.445
And prison will be the end of him.

1451
01:04:33.605 --> 01:04:34.965
What are you going to do?

1452
01:04:35.285 --> 01:04:37.445
I'm going to turn myself in.

1453
01:04:38.565 --> 01:04:40.485
(BIRDS TWEETING)

1454
01:04:42.965 --> 01:04:44.245
Wait.

1455
01:04:44.645 --> 01:04:46.965
(CURIOUS MUSIC)
Dogger. what's that on your neck?

1456
01:04:47.365 --> 01:04:48.565
Oh. I..

1457
01:04:48.965 --> 01:04:50.885
I got it the night I blacked out.

1458
01:04:52.005 --> 01:04:53.765
May I have a look?

1459
01:04:56.405 --> 01:04:57.765
(SIGHS)

1460
01:04:58.085 --> 01:04:59.605
(CLEARS THROAT)

1461
01:05:00.405 --> 01:05:02.005
(TENSE NOTE)

1462
01:05:02.325 --> 01:05:03.605
Dogger.

1463
01:05:03.685 --> 01:05:05.045
You didn't black out.

1464
01:05:05.365 --> 01:05:06.885
You were nobbed.

1465
01:05:07.045 --> 01:05:08.085
I was?

1466
01:05:08.405 --> 01:05:10.005
Someone hit you on the neck.

1467
01:05:10.325 --> 01:05:11.845
With a shoe. by the looks of it.

1468
01:05:11.925 --> 01:05:13.205
But if I really was knocked out.

1469
01:05:13.605 --> 01:05:14.885
then I-
You couldn't have killed anyone.

1470
01:05:15.285 --> 01:05:16.885
(CURIOUS MUSIC BUILDS)

1471
01:05:17.285 --> 01:05:20.325
(GASPS) Dogger.
do you know where the Rook's End is?

1472
01:05:21.205 --> 01:05:23.525
(EXCITING MUSIC)

1473
01:05:25.925 --> 01:05:27.125
(MUSIC STOPS)

1474
01:05:27.525 --> 01:05:29.045
(F AINT SINGING)
(LIVELY PIANO MUSIC)

1475
01:05:29.445 --> 01:05:30.725
MAN: # And smile

1476
01:05:30.885 --> 01:05:32.805
# Smile. smile #
(PIANO STOPS)

1477
01:05:32.965 --> 01:05:34.485
(ECHOES) Hey there! Are you lost?

1478
01:05:34.885 --> 01:05:36.965
Um... Come join us
'Til the nurse comes back.

1479
01:05:37.445 --> 01:05:38.405
(PIANO RESUMES)
(QUIETLY) Drat.

1480
01:05:38.805 --> 01:05:41.685
Next. a little love song from
America. I hope you like it.

1481
01:05:41.845 --> 01:05:43.285
(PLAYS "YOU BELONG TO ME"
BY JO STAFFORD)

1482
01:05:43.685 --> 01:05:45.765
# See the pyramids

1483
01:05:46.085 --> 01:05:49.285
# Along the Nile

1484
01:05:50.405 --> 01:05:54.965
# Watch the sun rise
On a tropic isle

1485
01:05:55.285 --> 01:05:56.805
(WIND GUSTING)

1486
01:05:57.045 --> 01:05:59.205
(SONG CONTINUES ON GRAMOPHONE)
JO STAFFORD: # Just remember

1487
01:05:59.605 --> 01:06:02.805
# When a dream appears

1488
01:06:02.885 --> 01:06:08.005
# You belong to me

1489
01:06:08.085 --> 01:06:10.245
(GRAMOPHONE VERSION FADES OUT)

1490
01:06:10.405 --> 01:06:12.325
May I be of assistance?

1491
01:06:12.725 --> 01:06:15.525
# Be so alone..
I'm here to see Dr Kissing.

1492
01:06:15.685 --> 01:06:17.765
Dr Isaac Kissing?
Yes.

1493
01:06:18.165 --> 01:06:20.405
Do you keep more than one?

1494
01:06:20.485 --> 01:06:22.165
In the solarium.

1495
01:06:22.325 --> 01:06:24.245
at the end of the hall.
# You'll be

1496
01:06:24.325 --> 01:06:27.445
# Lonesome

1497
01:06:27.525 --> 01:06:29.765
# Too

1498
01:06:30.165 --> 01:06:32.005
# And blue... #

1499
01:06:32.405 --> 01:06:34.885
(SONG STOPS ABRUPTLY)
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

1500
01:06:35.765 --> 01:06:37.525
(F AINT INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1501
01:06:37.925 --> 01:06:39.365
Dr Kissing?

1502
01:06:39.445 --> 01:06:40.485
Huh?

1503
01:06:40.885 --> 01:06:42.085
Ah! (CHUCKLING) Oh-ho!

1504
01:06:43.765 --> 01:06:45.605
Flavia!

1505
01:06:45.685 --> 01:06:47.365
I've been expecting you.

1506
01:06:47.525 --> 01:06:49.765
So. you're Jacko's daughter.

1507
01:06:50.165 --> 01:06:51.605
(CHUCKLES)

1508
01:06:51.685 --> 01:06:53.205
You don't look a bit like him.

1509
01:06:53.365 --> 01:06:56.485
I'm- I'm told I take after my mother.

1510
01:06:56.565 --> 01:06:59.125
Quite so. A remarkable woman.

1511
01:06:59.525 --> 01:07:01.045
You knew her?

1512
01:07:01.365 --> 01:07:02.885
Well. slightly.

1513
01:07:03.045 --> 01:07:04.245
